	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've been playing EQ for over two years now.<BR>
<BR>
I had, like everyone else, times when I'd thought of not playing any more. For me the reasons were based on the games mechanics; how, no matter what level you were, it basically boiled down to the fact that you spent time finding a group and then numerous hours &quot;camping&quot;...fighting the same things over and over again for experience or loot (you hoped). The game became rather bland to me and it was during these times I considered just giving up all together. What kept me playing though....was the cost. I realized that for $10 a month you couldnt beat it. I cant go to see one movie for less then that. The price was always right and I figured that maybe if I didnt quit altogether i could, at least, play less and STILL get my $10 worth.<BR>
<BR>
Now they are offering the very things I thought the game lacks.....for a price.<BR>
<BR>
I don't disagree with the reasoning behind it. I remember having to pay as much as $150 a month to have LIMITED access to an online computer game some 10 years ago (back when this kind of thing was new). To this day I still cant believe this game is only $10 a month.<BR>
<BR>
I would imagine this cant last forever though. The question you all need to ask yourselves is, &quot;am I willing to pay more to have more?&quot;. What price is TO much for you to pay to play EQ per month? $15? $20? $25?<BR>
<BR>
I think this is a question Verant should have asked. Instead of segregating &quot;service&quot; and &quot;features&quot; to only those people on new high-priced servers they maybe should have asked everyone if maybe increasing the monthly rate to, say, $15 a month would have been more beneficial. Then we ALL would have the service and new features and Verant would have the income to support it.<BR>
<BR>
But maybe they couldnt possibly get enough resources to support EVERYONE with those features described in the Legends servers? Maybe having everyone benefit from those features just isnt possible....no matter the cost to us?<BR>
<BR>
I think the cost of being on a Legends server is to much for those people to pay (I wont pay it, thats for sure) and that the cost for the rest of us to play on regular servers IS amazingly low. Maybe somewhere in between those prices they could have come up with a monthly cost we'd all agree on so that we all could have the benefits of the new servers?<BR>
<BR>
Like I said the $10 monthly fee is a great thing but what if, instead, I paid $12 a month? I could live with that and assuming they have roughly 400,000 paying customers now at $10 a month.....just paying 2 more bucks a month from us would generate an extra $800,000 a month for them (roughly). Would that be enough to have ALL of us on &quot;Legends&quot; servers? I dont know.<BR>
<BR>
I think that they could have gone about it differently and maybe we all would have benefited instead of most of us paying dirt cheap prices for regular servers and others paying out the butt for &quot;better&quot; servers.<BR>
<BR>
Just a thought.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
